2. Category selection: For every of the three commands given to the robot, the team
chooses the desired command category.
3. Operator:
Âˆ The person operating the robot is one of the referees (default operator).
Âˆ If the robot appears to consistently not be able to understand the operator, the
referees ask the team to continue with a custom operator or apply the CONTINUE
rule (Section 3.8.15).
Âˆ With the custom operator, the team can only score 50% of the points for the respective
command.
4. Retrieving the command: The robot must show it has understood the given command
by repeating the command (i.e. stating all the required information to accomplish the
task.).
5.4.4. Referee and OC instructions
2h before test:
Âˆ Specify and announce the entrance and exit door
